Ubuntu Install

Insert and lock the removable hard drive
Power on the computer
Insert CD
Press F1, when prompted ("SATA Cabling Error")
Select English with arrow keys and Enter
Press F3 to select the correct keymap (Finland)
Press Enter to boot the Live CD ("Try Ubuntu without any change to your computer")
Double-click the "Install" icon on the desktop

Welcome
  Select English as the install language
Where are you?
  Select the correct timezone by clicking on Finland in the map
Keyboard Layout
  The suggested keyboard layout should be "Finland", if not change it now
Prepare disk space
  Choose "Use the entire disk"
  Make sure you select the correct disk. Do NOT install on the internal HDD
Who are you?
  Enter your name, a username and a password.
  You can name the computer as you like.
  Choose "Require a password to log in"
Ready to Install
  Check the selected options and click "Install"
Remove CD and reboot when asked to do so.


Updates

Go to System => Administration => Update Manager
Click "Check", then "Install Updates"
Close the Update Manager once it's done


Install Komodo Edit

Open http://www.activestate.com/komodo_edit in Firefox
Click "Download now" in the upper right corner
Choose "Save File" and click OK
You can close Firefox once the download has completed
Right click on the Komodo-Edit file on the Desktop
Select "Extract here"
Open Terminal (Applications => Accessories => Terminal)
Enter these commands (use the Tab key to autocomplete paths and file names):
cd Desktop/Komodo-Edit-5.2.1-4108-linux-libcpp6-x86
sudo sh install.sh
Install Directory: /opt/Komodo-Edit-5
Press Enter to install



Install Ruby, Ruby Gems and Rails

Open Terminal again:
sudo apt-get install -y ruby-full libsqlite3-ruby libsqlite3-dev build-essential
wget http://rubyforge.org/frs/download.php/60718/rubygems-1.8.5.tgz
tar -xvf rubygems-1.3.5.tgz
cd rubygems-1.3.5
sudo ruby setup.rb
sudo ln -s /usr/bin/gem1.8 /usr/bin/gem
sudo gem install rails mongrel
